        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-23T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-23T01:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2–2347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-23T14:00:00+08:00">February 23, 1947—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 23—4:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>348. Rumor has it, as is reported in the press, that Foreign Minister’s trip to
                    North China will include Manchuria where he will allegedly undertake discussions
                    with Russian authorities. For obvious reasons (Embtel 336, February 21) Embassy
                    has not attempted to check on this rumor. Embassy has, however, reliable info
                    that while in Peiping Wang Shih-chieh will discuss on Gimo’s behalf
                    participation in a reorganized government of Hu Shih<note n="72" xml:id="d37fn1">Former Chinese Ambassador in the United States and at this time president
                        of Peita University at Peiping.</note> and certain other individuals
                    resident in that area.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
